    <text id="A9202T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>In this brief note, Tyler &amp; Son asks Enos for provisions and informs him
                    of their receipt of his check.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Messrs, A &amp; E. Ott<lb/>Moffetts Creek<lb/>Augusta Co. Va.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-05-19">May 19, 1864</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir<hi rend="super">s</hi>:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your Check to hand for $450.40 We have been very busy with the wounded the last
                    few days. We want all kinds of provisions here very badly Send what you can of
                    any kind</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Most <abbr expan="Respectfully">Resply</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>Tyler &amp; Son</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
